From 6cfeb6cd8917ef7f6662dd7cc40336d09d26d010 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Carter Chen <carterchan50@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Apr 2026 06:59:44 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 06/11] brcmfmac/hwsim: add brcmfmac_hwsim module with complete
 ioctl table
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Implement the virtual firmware + hardware bus module (brcmfmac_hwsim.ko):

Core components:
- BCDC dcmd parser: extracts cmd, reqid, ifidx, set/get flag, payload
- BCDC response builder: sets correct flags, status, request ID matching
- Comprehensive ioctl/iovar handler table:
  * Probe-FATAL: cur_etheraddr, ver, mpc, event_msgs GET/SET,
    SCAN_CHANNEL_TIME, SCAN_UNASSOC_TIME
  * Non-fatal: REVINFO, cap, clmver, join_pref, txbf [D3-D5]
  * Feature detection: pfn/wowl/rsdb/tdls/sup_wpa return
  * Scan: escan, chanspec, bw_cap, rxchain, nmode, vhtmode
  * Connect: join, SET_SSID, wpa_auth/auth/wsec/wpaie
  * AP mode: SET_AP, SET_INFRA, UP/DOWN, SET_SSID events
  * Default: unknown GET → BCME_UNSUPPORTED, unknown SET → success
- Scan event generator (workqueue-based): partial + complete events
- Connect event generator: BRCMF_E_LINK with LINK flag
- Data TX→RX loopback converter
- Firmware download handler (fw_download → FW_BOOTED)
- EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(brcmf_hwsim_get_ops) for symbol_get() IPC

Error code system: all BCDC responses use Broadcom firmware error
codes (BCME_*) in the status field, not Linux errno values.

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
